{
  "text": "It was shown in [CITATION_1] that every \u03d5 \u2208 S m induces a bounded composition operator on each of the spaces H 2 m,\u03b2 , satisfying a \"one-variable style\" norm estimate, in particular an estimate which depends only on the value of \u03d5 at 0. In fact when m = 1 this is precisely the \"classical\" norm estimate for composition operators on the standard scale of Hilbert function spaces. In higher dimensions, a related upper bound was obtained by Bayart [4, Theorem 4.1], which applies to certain univalent mappings (not necessarily in S m ) but which depends both on \u03d5(0) and on global estimates for derivatives of \u03d5. ",
  "citation_candidates": [
